  "texts": [
    "This approach involves introducing domain-specific parameters, referred to as adapters, into pretrained models.",
    "These adapters, which are made of small neural networks, are strategically inserted within or between the layers of the pretrained model.",
    "During the training process, only the parameters of these added adapters are updated, while the parameters of the pretrained model remain unchanged 7.",
    "While adapters provide a more simple approach, they may not fully capture complex data patterns as effectively as fine-tuning the entire model.",
    "In addition, determining the optimal locations to insert adapters within the LLM can be challenging and may require experimentation."
  ],
